- Yeah.

43:29.399 --> 43:31.900
All right, the ethics of Wade
coming on the show,

43:31.985 --> 43:33.819
that was fair. You had every right to run that.

43:33.903 --> 43:35.946
But to say that
she almost got someone killed...

43:36.030 --> 43:39.616
I'm running a piece
saying you hired an incompetent EP

43:39.701 --> 43:41.368
because she was your girlfriend,
and she dumped you.

43:41.452 --> 43:43.662
I hired the best EP in broadcasting

43:43.746 --> 43:45.831
in spite of her being my ex-girlfriend
who dumped me.

43:45.915 --> 43:48.792
You know,
you guys up there are millionaires...

43:48.876 --> 43:51.753
- I'm the only millionaire up there.
...and celebrities.

43:51.838 --> 43:54.089
- I'm the only celebrity up there.
- Not anymore.

43:54.173 --> 43:55.882
How does this work?

43:56.843 --> 44:00.721
I'm thinking about investing in a restaurant,

44:02.098 --> 44:05.809
and I'm looking for silent partners.
$50,000 a share.

44:05.893 --> 44:08.729
- $50,000, and I'm a silent partner?
- Yes.

44:08.813 --> 44:11.064
- And you're a silent partner?
- Quiet as a mouse.

44:11.149 --> 44:13.233
- For good?
- You'll have your own table

44:13.318 --> 44:15.277
at the restaurant for life.

44:23.536 --> 44:24.911
Hey, Will,

44:26.748 --> 44:28.332
we're journalists.

44:32.795 --> 44:34.838
- I wish you hadn't said that.
- What?

44:34.922 --> 44:37.841
Everything would have been cool if you
hadn't said that. You just talk too much.

44:37.925 --> 44:40.802
You have a problem
with me calling myself a journalist?

44:40.887 --> 44:45.640
Only the elite few who cover stories
nobody cares about get to call themselves...

44:45.725 --> 44:49.227
I've got a guy on my staff got hit
in the head with a glass door Thursday.

44:49.312 --> 44:52.022
His forehead wouldn't stop bleeding,
but he wouldn't go to a doctor,

44:52.106 --> 44:54.399
'cause I got another guy
who got beat up covering Cairo.

44:54.484 --> 44:57.986
And the first guy wouldn't see a doctor
until the second guy saw a doctor.

44:58.071 --> 45:02.032
I've got a producer who ran into a locked door
'cause he felt responsible for the second guy.

45:02.116 --> 45:05.702
I've got an 18-year-old kid risking his life
halfway around the world,

45:05.787 --> 45:08.830
and the AP who sent him there
hasn't slept in three days.

45:08.915 --> 45:12.459
I've got 20-somethings
who care about teachers in Wisconsin.

45:12.543 --> 45:15.295
I've got a grown woman
who has to subtract with her fingers

45:15.380 --> 45:17.714
staying up all night trying to learn economics

45:17.799 --> 45:21.760
from a PhD who could be making
20 times the money three miles downtown.

45:21.844 --> 45:23.053
They're journalists.

45:24.639 --> 45:28.058
Come after me all you want, Nina.
Come after me every day.

45:28.142 --> 45:29.226
Look through my garbage.

45:29.310 --> 45:32.396
Invent things out of thin air.
That's what you're paid for.

45:32.480 --> 45:36.566
But you touch my staff,
and you are walking into a world of hurt.

45:36.651 --> 45:42.114
I have an hour of prime time every night,
and I will rededicate my life to ruining yours.

45:43.658 --> 45:46.201
I also want you to send a message
up the chain

45:46.285 --> 45:48.912
of whatever backroom machinery
is driving this

45:48.996 --> 45:53.250
that if I so much as smell Leona Lansing's
perfume on any of this,

45:53.334 --> 45:57.838
I'm going to make a meal out of both of you,
and I won't stop until I'm done.

45:58.506 --> 46:00.006
Look at me.

46:01.926 --> 46:03.927
And see that I'm dead serious.

46:12.186 --> 46:14.104
Restaurants are bad investments.

46:14.772 --> 46:17.315
Wait 20 minutes before you leave here.

46:19.110 --> 46:21.027
Tough-ass speech.

46:23.406 --> 46:25.157
- But you're not gonna win.
- I don't care.

46:25.241 --> 46:28.410
I'm just a middle-aged man
who never lived up to his potential.

46:28.494 --> 46:31.705
You don't want to be on the wrong end of me
if I ever do.

46:31.789 --> 46:33.039
I got the drinks.

46:35.376 --> 46:39.963
1980, Ronald Reagan is elected president,
and the culture of deregulation begins.

46:40.047 --> 46:43.008
What happened to Will?
I haven't seen him around.

46:43.092 --> 46:46.386
- He changed and ran out right after the show.
- Where?

46:47.054 --> 46:50.015
The culture of deregulation culminates
in 1999.

46:50.099 --> 46:52.934
- Glass-Steagall gets repealed.
- And immediately banks start merging.

46:53.019 --> 46:56.855
Now, Gordon Gekko can use
George Bailey's bank balance to make bets.

46:56.939 --> 46:58.356
Where's James Harper?

46:58.774 --> 47:00.567
That's Lisa.

47:01.694 --> 47:03.236
- Oh, my God!
- Oh, my God.

47:04.614 --> 47:06.490
It's Valentine's Day. I forgot to meet her.

47:06.574 --> 47:08.992
James Harper? Nobody?

47:09.076 --> 47:11.620
If he is not here, I will stand here...

47:11.704 --> 47:12.913
- What are you doing?
- Hiding.

47:12.997 --> 47:15.165
- Does this seem like a good plan to you?
- No.

47:15.249 --> 47:16.458
- Get up.
- Please don't make me.

47:16.542 --> 47:17.667
Get up!

47:19.253 --> 47:22.797
But I'm looking for Jim
because he did not come.

47:22.882 --> 47:24.883
- Anyone? James?
- Lisa.

47:24.967 --> 47:27.010
I am so sorry. It's been a very chaotic day.

47:27.094 --> 47:28.803
Where the fuck have you been?

47:31.140 --> 47:33.016
- Like I said, it's been...
- You don't know how to use a phone?

47:33.100 --> 47:36.770
I might have a concussion, but still I'm sorry.

47:36.854 --> 47:39.648
You're sorry?
All right, in that case, I totally forgive you

47:39.732 --> 47:41.983
for making me wait alone
in a restaurant for an hour.

47:42.068 --> 47:43.610
I appreciate that.

47:43.694 --> 47:45.070
- Unless you're being sarcastic.
- She was.

47:45.154 --> 47:46.404
I thought there was an outside chance...

47:46.489 --> 47:47.781
- Did you get any of my messages?
- No.

47:47.865 --> 47:49.241
- Wait, are you Lisa?
- Yes.

47:49.325 --> 47:50.784
- I got your messages.
- What?

47:50.868 --> 47:52.452
We accidentally switched phones again.

47:52.537 --> 47:53.954
What happened to marking them
with nail polish?

47:54.038 --> 47:55.247
We both did that.

47:55.331 --> 47:57.415
You stood me up on Valentine's Day,

47:57.500 --> 47:59.626
which is 1,000 times worse
than a regular stand up.

47:59.710 --> 48:01.378
- I didn't stand you up.
- Yes, you did.

48:01.462 --> 48:04.714
Yes, I did, but I have presents,

48:05.424 --> 48:07.842
and I wrote you a card.

48:10.888 --> 48:12.097
"From the desk of James Harper."

48:12.181 --> 48:13.723
- Are you kidding?
- I lost the card.

48:13.808 --> 48:15.308
- You're a jerk.
- No, he's not.

48:15.393 --> 48:16.560
- Maggie.
- Lisa, stop.

48:16.644 --> 48:18.144
- You know what?
- Stop!

48:18.646 --> 48:20.313
Jim did everything right here.

48:20.398 --> 48:22.148
Well, he left me alone in a restaurant
for an hour.

48:22.233 --> 48:23.358
- Except that.
- And didn't call.

48:23.442 --> 48:25.485
- And that.
- It would be hard for a casual observer

48:25.570 --> 48:27.070
- to tell which side...
- Shut up.

48:27.154 --> 48:29.656
Lisa, he's a very decent guy.

48:29.740 --> 48:32.409
- This isn't anyone's fault.
- It's his.

48:32.493 --> 48:36.538
It's a little bit his,
but mostly it's just a very bad day.

48:36.622 --> 48:39.958
It's Valentine's Day. It's my favorite day.

48:40.042 --> 48:41.876
Then pick another day!

48:42.336 --> 48:44.087
Because it's every guy's least favorite day.

48:44.171 --> 48:45.922
Everyone's always disappointed.

48:46.007 --> 48:48.925
Valentine's Day is the bully of holidays.

48:49.385 --> 48:51.261
It forces love on people who aren't in love.

48:51.345 --> 48:52.596
- Cupid's freakish.
- All right.

48:52.680 --> 48:55.765
No, I'm boycotting Valentine's Day
from now on.

48:55.850 --> 48:57.350
Who's with me?

49:00.688 --> 49:02.856
I love you every day.

49:02.940 --> 49:06.401
Today's just an excuse
to spend the night in a hotel room.

49:08.529 --> 49:10.488
I'm sorry. I was faking it just then.

49:10.740 --> 49:12.824
I think she can still hear you.

49:15.703 --> 49:17.287
I'm sorry.

49:18.581 --> 49:20.707
I'm really sorry.

49:23.461 --> 49:26.129
I'm still wearing edible underwear.

49:26.213 --> 49:27.297
Well, if I'd known that...

49:27.381 --> 49:28.923
Shut up!

49:31.052 --> 49:34.179
It's one big Jenga tower.
You pull a piece out, put it on top,

49:34.263 --> 49:37.557
and the tower definitely gets higher,
but also gets less stable.

49:38.434 --> 49:39.809
Will's back.

49:42.897 --> 49:44.189
Let's do this.

49:47.193 --> 49:48.193
Oi.

49:55.785 --> 49:57.911
- Where have you been?
- I had to run an errand.

49:57.995 --> 50:00.497
- What kind of errand?
- I wanted some gum. Got it.

50:01.248 --> 50:02.374
Let me tell you something, Billy.

50:02.458 --> 50:04.542
I ever find out you paid
a gossip columnist money

50:04.627 --> 50:08.505
to protect me, I will beat you senseless.
And you know I can do it, because I'm crafty.

50:08.589 --> 50:09.589
I know.

50:09.674 --> 50:11.257
- Do you understand?
- Yeah.

50:13.344 --> 50:15.220
I hear Corporate wired the money.

50:15.304 --> 50:17.305
- Kahlid's home.
- Yeah.

50:17.390 --> 50:21.017
Funny, because legal wouldn't even let us talk
to our own security about Kahlid

50:21.102 --> 50:23.186
- because of the exposure.
- They changed their mind.

50:23.270 --> 50:24.270
Hmm.

50:25.815 --> 50:29.859
Did you know that it was Bill Clinton
who signed the repeal of Glass-Steagall?

50:29.944 --> 50:31.486
Yeah, everybody knows that.

50:31.570 --> 50:34.447
Well, now everybody knows it.

50:35.991 --> 50:37.033
How are the lessons going?

50:37.118 --> 50:39.786
Corporate didn't wire anything. You did.

50:43.124 --> 50:45.125
He's one of our guys.

50:47.294 --> 50:48.294
Yeah.

50:51.465 --> 50:53.299
Speaking of which...

51:01.142 --> 51:03.309
It's not much, but I'd like to help with this.

51:03.394 --> 51:06.646
- Neal, you can't afford it.
- Please.

51:08.441 --> 51:09.899
Sure. Thank you.

51:14.029 --> 51:17.365
All right, so I...

51:20.161 --> 51:21.995
- It's not much.
- Maggie.

51:22.079 --> 51:23.329
Please.

51:24.749 --> 51:26.040
What's this in the memo line?

51:26.125 --> 51:27.584
Read it.

51:28.419 --> 51:29.794
"Coach."

52:22.556 --> 52:24.390
We want Rudy to dress for the game, Coach.

52:24.475 --> 52:26.392
You guys are missing your fife and drum.

52:40.741 --> 52:42.367
You did this?

52:43.077 --> 52:45.036
Happy Valentine's Day.
